description: Multi-step strategy that finds cases who are less than 24 months of age that are only positive for Giardia and reported a duration of diarrhea more than than 3 days.
Giardia positive controls, normal at baseline, who have <-2 HAZ @60 Day Follow-Up
Giardia + Cases who have a Giardia - Control

Multi-step strategy that returns Case participants who were only positive for Giardia and no other pathogen and had a diarrhea duration of less than 4 days. Step 1: Selects cases less than 24 months of age who are Giardia positive Step 2: Removes all cases who are positive for any other pathogen Step 3: Selects those with duration less than 4 days.
Households containing two children <= 5 observed for at least 365 days, one who had 0 malaria diagnoses and another who had at least 1 malaria diagnosis / yr during observation.

For calendar years 2012-2013, find all Children aged 2-10 who were observed at least 365 days and live in households where <= 5 mosquitoes were collected on average in 2012-13 and had at least 2 malaria=yes visits / year. Of those, how many had at least one asymptomatic visit in that time frame.
Finds the middle visit of three consecutive asymptomatic visits among children where a pbmc sample is available from the middle visit

For calendar years 2012-2013, find all Children aged 2-10 who were observed at least 180 days in that time period and live in households where >= 10 mosquitoes were collected on average in 2012-13 but who had 0 malaria=yes visits / year. Of those, how many had at least one asymptomatic visit in that time frame.
